title: Falcon Heavy set to launch its fifth flight of 2023 with X-37B aboard
summary: As 2023 draws to a close, the US Department of Defense’s X-37B spaceplane is being prepared to return to space on the OTV-7 mission aboard a SpaceX Falcon Heavy rocket. USSF-52, the fifth Falcon Heavy flight of the year, and ninth overall, is scheduled to fly on Monday, Dec. 11, 2023, at 8:14 PM EST (01:14 UTC Dec. 12) from pad 39A at the Kennedy Space Center at the start of a 10-minute launch window.

title: NASA's MAVEN Observes the Disappearing Solar Wind
summary: NASA’s MAVEN (Mars Atmosphere and Volatile EvolutioN) mission observed the dramatic and unexpected “disappearance” of a stream of charged particles constantly emanating off the Sun, known as the solar wind.

title: China’s reusable rocket race heats up with new hop test
summary: Launch startup iSpace has successfully launched and landed a test article, a month after a first hop test, as Chinese reusable rocket efforts intensify.

title: Helicity Space raises $5 million for fusion engine development
summary: Helicity Space, a California startup developing fusion engines, has raised $5 million in a seed funding round.

title: Space Force chief tempers expectations: ‘Go government fast, not SpaceX fast’
summary: Since its inception four years ago, the U.S. Space Force has faced congressional scrutiny and received numerous directives to transform the military’s space capabilities at warp speed.
